				<p>Hi&#8230; this is a belated comment, but I am about the make this cake tonight. I am looking at your recipe and it says 6 tbsp sour cream. The original recipe called for 1 1/3 cup. 1 1/3 cup = 16 tbsp + (5 tbsp + 1 tsp) ~ 21 tbsp, right? Then in half that would be just over 10 tbsp. Maybe I&#8217;m making a really dumb mistake on the math &#8211; let me know!! Besides, I&#8217;m sure it would come out great either way</p>
