<li class="commentbody highlighted" id="comment-190940">
			<cite><a href='http://smittenkitchen.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>deb</a></cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-190940" title="">October 27, 2008</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">74</div>

				<p>They are white chocolate discs for baking from Guittard. At the time, Fresh Direct kept sending me the wrong chocolate (white when I ordered dark) so I had a collection of them. As soon as you drape the ganache, while it is still warm, you can put the white chocolate pieces in and they&#8217;ll meld with the dark chocolate to become smooth.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
<li class="commentbody" id="comment-190941">
