				<p>For the &#8220;ganache&#8221;  &#8211; I prefer just to put some semi-sweet chocolate, or unsweetened chocolate in a double boiler &#8211; and simply add Bailey&#8217;s or Khalua until the consistency becomes smooth. Then simply drizzle that over the top. It also hardens a bit and give a nice texture. The Bailey&#8217;s/Khalua is a nice touch to compliment the Guinness. Enjoy!</p>
