				<p>Wendy &#8212; You might look into something called a <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0000VM82M?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=smitten-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B0000VM82M" rel="nofollow">heating core</a> which helps large cake bake evenly. Some <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000I1UXUI?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=smitten-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B000I1UXUI" rel="nofollow">strips around the pan</a> will help it stay flat, as will baking it at a lower temperature. You might enjoy my <a href="http://smittenkitchen.com/2009/03/layer-cake-tips-the-biggest-birthday-cake-yet/" rel="nofollow">layer cake tips</a> as well.</p>
